ombine <b>5 sec\/\/speed 3<b>."},{"content":"Roll 1 tablespoon of mixture into a ball and place onto prepared baking tray. Repeat with remaining mixture (makes approx. 20 balls). Spray with oil and bake for 15 minutes (200°C), turning twice, until golden brown. Once cooked, transfer into a thermal serving bowl or other large bowl and cover to keep warm. Proceed with recipe while tempeh balls are cooking. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place oil, ginger, onion and remaining 2 garlic cloves into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>."},{"content":"Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and cook <b>3 min\/120°C\/speed 2<b>, <strong>without measuring cup.<\/strong> "},{"content":"Add carrot, capsicum, corn and pineapple and cook <b>6 min\/120°C\/\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add tomatoes, snow peas, coconut sugar, vinegar, cornflour, salt and pepper to taste and remaining 1 tablespoon tamari and cook <b>6-8 min\/90°C\/\/speed 1<b> or until vegetables are cooked to your liking. Transfer vegetables into thermal serving bowl with tempeh balls and combine to coat. Serve warm (see Tips)."}],"hintsAndTricks":["We recommend using an unmarinated tempeh in this recipe.","Be sure to check the label of your tamari, as not all brands are gluten free.","You can replace the fresh baby corn with rinsed and drained canned baby corn.","We served ours with steamed jasmine rice."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","50m","4 portions"]}